# Frontend environment variables (Vite) — TEMPLATE.
#
# IMPORTANT: every variable prefixed with VITE_ is inlined into the client
# bundle and shipped to the browser — it is PUBLIC. Never put a secret
# (API secret, password, private token) in this file or in a real .env.
#
# The app currently needs no build-time env vars: all configuration is fetched
# from the backend at runtime (e.g. the Cloudinary upload signature endpoint),
# so the Cloudinary api_secret never reaches the client.
#
# Example (uncomment and set only if a genuinely public flag is ever needed):
# VITE_SOME_PUBLIC_FLAG=true
